message.content:
Sure! Here's an example code that meets your requirements:

HTML:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Stylish Dialog</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <button id="showDialog">Open Dialog</button>

    <div id="dialog" class="dialog">
        <div class="dialog-content">
            <button id="closeDialog" class="close">X</button>
            <h2>Please Enter Your Name</h2>
            <input type="text" id="userInput" placeholder="Enter your name">
            <button id="okBtn">OK</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

CSS (styles.css):
```css
body {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    background-color: #333;
}

.dialog {
    display: none;
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);
    z-index: 9999;
}

.dialog-content {
    background-color: #fff;
    width: 300px;
    margin: 100px auto;
    padding: 20px;
    position: relative;
}

.close {
    position: absolute;
    top: 10px;
    right: 10px;
    border: none;
    background: none;
    font-size: 18px;
    cursor: pointer;
    color: #555;
}

h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
}

input[type="text"] {
    width: 100%;
    padding: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
}

button {
    padding: 10px 20px;
    background-color: #555;
    border: none;
    color: #fff;
    cursor: pointer;
}

button:hover {
    background-color: #333;
}
```

JavaScript (script.js):
```js
document.getElementById("showDialog").addEventListener("click", function() {
  document.getElementById("dialog").style.display = "block";
});

document.getElementById("closeDialog").addEventListener("click", function() {
  document.getElementById("dialog").style.display = "none";
});

document.getElementById("okBtn").addEventListener("click", function() {
  var userInput = document.getElementById("userInput").value;
  if (userInput !== "") {
    console.log("User entered: " + userInput);
    document.getElementById("dialog").style.display = "none";
  } else {
    alert("Please enter your name!");
  }
});
```

When the "Open Dialog" button is clicked, it will display a stylish dialog box asking the user to enter their name. If the user enters a value and clicks on "OK", it will log the input in the console and close the dialog. If no value is entered, it displays an alert message. The dialog has a dark background and the web page is responsive.
